  "prompt": "What's the definition of vote margin?",
  "response": "Vote margin, also known as margin of victory, is the difference between the number of votes received by the winning candidate and the number of votes received by the candidate who came in second place in an election. It is usually expressed as a percentage of the total votes cast or as an absolute number of votes. A larger vote margin indicates a more decisive win for the victorious candidate.",
